author: COMSOL
description: Transient model that simulates the filling of a narrow channel due to surface tension and wall adhesion. The capillary channel is initially filled with air. Because it is attached to a water reservoir, capillary forces cause water to rise through the channel. The contact angle, the angle between the water surface and the wall, is fixed to 67.5 degrees. The model can be solved using either a level set or a phase field method to track the fluid interface. This example uses the phase field method.
label: capillary_filling_pf.mph
